	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It isn't necessarily the best <em>signal</em> possible or nearly the best circuit by default since it needs the specific Japanese transistor and sounds like it needs the ferrite choke. Has it been compared to other GENERIC small signal transistor amplifiers? I bet any common collector amp with that same transistor would perform the same. Before people hail Nintendo's cheap circuit as the end all, realize that a 2N3904 could be biased for the desired 1Vpp into 75ohms output.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


